# Git attributes for GA (Guitar Alchemist)
#
# Git-LFS tracking for large binary assets. The first asset to live
# here is the GEBCO 2023 bathymetry texture used by the Prime Radiant
# ocean renderer. See docs/brainstorms/2026-04-11-planet-ocean-zoom-v3-
# production-spec.md for the full rationale.
#
# Adopting LFS affects every future clone of this repo: developers
# need `git-lfs` installed to fetch the actual binary content
# (placeholder text is stored in plain git). Setup:
#   git lfs install      # one-time per developer machine
#   git lfs pull         # one-time after first clone if LFS was
#                        # added after the developer cloned
#
# If GitHub's LFS bandwidth quota becomes a concern (1 GB/month free,
# 50 GB/month paid), move large assets to tile-on-demand from S3/CDN
# per the Phase 3 plan in the ocean spec.

# GEBCO bathymetry textures for the Prime Radiant ocean renderer.
# Narrow pattern — we do NOT want to sweep every PNG in the repo into
# LFS, only the large bathymetry assets under this specific path.
# The path matches where the existing 2k_earth_* textures already live
# in ReactComponents/ga-react-components/public/textures/planets/.
ReactComponents/ga-react-components/public/textures/planets/bathymetry_*.png filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
